5 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING THE COST FOR NONRESIDENT SMITH RIVER
6 BONUS POINTS; AMENDING SECTION 23-2-409, MCA; AND PROVIDING AN IMMEDIATE EFFECTIVE
7 DATE.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 Section 1. Section 23-2-409, MCA, is amended to read:
12 "23-2-409. Allocation of user fees -- expenditure of Smith River corridor enhancement account.
13 (1) All money collected as recreational and commercial user fees for floating and camping on the Smith River
14 waterway pursuant to 23-2-408 must be deposited in the state treasury in the Smith River corridor
15 enhancement account in the state special revenue fund to the credit of the department.
16 (2) (a) The following portions of recreational and commercial user fees deposited in the Smith
17 River corridor enhancement account must be used for the purposes in subsection (2)(b):
18 (i) $50 of each commercial outfitter client fee;
19 (ii) all revenue from the sale of super permit lottery chances;
20 (iii) all revenue from sales of a resident-only $5 bonus point and a nonresident $50 $125 bonus
21 point; and
22 (iv) 5% of other float fee revenue, except for the nonrefundable permit application fee.
23 (b) The sum of the funds described in subsection (2)(a) must be expended to:
24 (i) protect and enhance the integrity of the natural and scenic beauty of the Smith River waterway
25 and its recreational, fisheries, and wildlife values through the lease or acquisition of property, including lease or
26 acquisition of partial interests in property by the department within the Smith River corridor;
27 (ii) pursue projects that serve to protect, enhance, and restore fisheries habitat, streambank
28 stabilization, erosion control, and recreational values within the Smith River corridor, including Smith River
